				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I did my own implementation. I'm using Altera and not Xilinx. But in general, the scheme is taken from someone's working draft of a project, maybe even PowerPack. You should remember this: MMC3 on this scheme contain 6 8-bit CHR registers (used only 7 bit of each register) and 2 6-bit PRG registers. Also it require about 15 registers for IRQ. Every single bit uses 1 CPLD's register.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
